tfsec is a static analysis tool for terraform code to spot potential
misconfigurations and or security issues.

Checks for misconfigurations across all major cloud providers.
Hundreds of built-in rules.
Scans modules (local and remote)
Evaluates HCL expressions as well as literal values
Evaluates Terraform functions e.g. concat()
Evaluates relationships between Terraform resources
Applies (and embellishes) user-defined Rego policies
Supports multiple output formats:
  lovely (default), JSON, SARIF, CSV, CheckStyle, JUnit, text, Gif.
